
################################################################################### #
# Trickier cases of items git should ignore

/data/*.arrow
# The large datasets stored as .arrow files take up roughly 1 GB of storage space.
# They are downloaded from a separate repo (ejamdata) and
# get saved in the data folder when a user installs the package, but they are not part of the package itself per se.
# seee https://public-environmental-data-partners.github.io/EJAM/articles/dev-update-datasets.html

/data-raw/pipeline_outputs/
# Generated annual data-update pipeline checkpoints can include many large CSV
# files, such as raw ACS tables and derived blockgroupstats/bgej/usastats files.
# If a checkpoint folder should be committed temporarily, force-add it so the
# .gitattributes Git LFS rules apply.

tests/testthat/_snaps/
tests/testthat/_snaps/**/*.png
# Try ignoring the _snaps folders entirely, since they can
# take >400 MB for the snapshots created during webapp testing via shinytest2 package
# as explained in the "Testing EJAM App with shinytest2" vignette/article
# at https://public-environmental-data-partners.github.io/EJAM/articles/dev-run-shinytests.html

# /docs/
# These are NOT ignored, currently, although perhaps that could be reconsidered.
# The html etc. created by pkgdown for documentation of the package are in the /docs/ folders.
# The whole docs folder is only about 12 MB, but has thousands of files (which to be fair can be distracting to have git track and to commit change to).
# The repository was configured to deploy and publish the gh pages website from the docs folder,
# in which case we presumably do not want to ignore changes in it, despite defaults in pkgdown package?
# (The default is that use_pkgdown(): creates a pkgdown config file and adds relevant files or directories to .Rbuildignore and .gitignore to ignore the docs folder?)
# However, maybe gh actions can create and deploy the site (from a docs folder on github.com?) without one having to run EJAM:::pkgdown_update() locally and committing the local docs folders.

################################################################################### #
# Standard or obvious items to ignore


# History files
.Rhistory
.Rapp.history

# Session Data files and any .rda file accidentally saved in the root folder
.RData
/*.rda

# User-specific files
.Ruserdata

# Example code in package build process
*-Ex.R

# Output files from R CMD build
/*.tar.gz

# Output files from R CMD check
/*.Rcheck/

# RStudio files
.Rproj.user/
/.Rproj.user
*.pper

# Vignettes other than the type created by the pkgdown package.
# The .Rmd files in the vignettes folder get turned into html articles in the docs folder via EJAM:::pkgdown_update(),
# and we do not really need to build and install the traditional type of vignette R supports.
vignettes/*.html
vignettes/*.pdf

# knitr and R markdown default cache directories
*_cache/
/cache/

# Temporary files created by R markdown
*.utf8.md
*.knit.md

# OAuth2 token, see https://github.com/hadley/httr/releases/tag/v0.3
.httr-oauth

# R Environment Variables to ignore, not part of the released package.
.Renviron
*.Rproj
inst/doc
packrat/lib*/
*.dcf
# such as EJAM/rsconnect/rstudio-connect.dmap-stage.aws.epa.gov/..../ejam.dcf  configuration file for deplying to RStudio Connect server
/Meta/


# .DS_Store files are created by macOS to store Finder metadata/settings
.DS_Store
**/.DS_Store

# Ignore any bookmarks a developer might have created while using the app locally.
/shiny_bookmarks

# Ignore artifacts created while trying out plumber-based API locally
inst/plumber/log_api_usage*.txt
